## QUALITY CHECKLIST — Before submitting BRD

- [ ] Executive summary is jargon-free (non-technical client can understand it)
- [ ] Every user type is defined (not just "user")
- [ ] Every FR has acceptance criteria (no vague "system shall" language)
- [ ] All P0 items have clear, testable criteria
- [ ] Non-functional requirements are specific numbers (not "fast" or "scalable")
- [ ] Integrations list is complete with auth method noted
- [ ] Business rules are explicitly separated from UI decisions
- [ ] Out-of-scope items are explicitly listed
- [ ] Open questions are numbered and owned
- [ ] Data sensitivity classified (determines security requirements)
- [ ] No feature is listed without a user story connecting it to user value
